Comments are non-executable statements that provide explanations or annotations within the code.They are used to improve code
readability and help developers understand the purpose and functionality of the code.

Comments are ignored by the Java compiler during execution.

There are three types of Comments in Java: 

1. Single line comment - //
2. Multi line comment - 

/*
  This is a comment
*/

3. Documentation comment -

/**
  This is a documentation 
  comment. It is used to provide 
  documentation such as what a particular class or method is doing.
*/
